<topic id='element_episode_number__neonatal_critical_care_spell_.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: EPISODE NUMBER (NEONATAL CRITICAL CARE SPELL) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_episode_number__neonatal_critical_care_spell_">EPISODE NUMBER (NEONATAL CRITICAL CARE SPELL)</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_activity_identifier">ACTIVITY IDENTIFIER</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_episode_number__neonatal_critical_care_spell_">EPISODE NUMBER (NEONATAL CRITICAL CARE SPELL)</xref>
 is used to sequentially identify each 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_critical_care_period">CRITICAL CARE PERIOD</xref>
 within a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_neonatal_critical_care_spell">Neonatal Critical Care Spell</xref>. The first 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_critical_care_period">CRITICAL CARE PERIOD</xref>
 identifier commences at 1; subsequent 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_critical_care_period">CRITICAL CARE PERIODS</xref>
 during the same 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_neonatal_critical_care_spell">Neonatal Critical Care Spell</xref>
 (within the same or different 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Providers</xref>) are then incremented by 1.        </p>
      <p>For example:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
A 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_neonate">Neonate</xref>
 is admitted to the Neonatal Intensive Care Unit at Trust A, starting a 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_critical_care_period">CRITICAL CARE PERIOD</xref>
 and generating 
                                <xref outputclass="element"
                        keyref="element_episode_number__neonatal_critical_care_spell_">EPISODE NUMBER (NEONATAL CRITICAL CARE SPELL)</xref>
 1.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
The 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_neonate">Neonate</xref>
 is then transferred to a different 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_health_care_provider">Health Care Provider</xref>, Trust B (ending the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_critical_care_period">CRITICAL CARE PERIOD</xref>
 at Trust A), which generates 
                                <xref outputclass="element"
                        keyref="element_episode_number__neonatal_critical_care_spell_">EPISODE NUMBER (NEONATAL CRITICAL CARE SPELL)</xref>
 2.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
The 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_neonate">Neonate</xref>
 may then return to Trust A (ending the 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_critical_care_period">CRITICAL CARE PERIOD</xref>
 at Trust B), generating 
                                <xref outputclass="element"
                        keyref="element_episode_number__neonatal_critical_care_spell_">EPISODE NUMBER (NEONATAL CRITICAL CARE SPELL)</xref>
 3.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
  </div>
</body>
